Contact Information
Company name:    Poma Construction
Contact name:    Michelle Damone
Job title:    Business Development Director
Mobile:    (561) 315-2973
Email:    michelle@pomaonline.com
Website:    http://www.pomaonline.com
Address:    2049 Southwest Poma Drive
City:    Palm City
State:    FL
ZIP code:    34990
Country:    United States
Timestamp:    3/9/16 10:30 CST
 
Company Profile
Segment:    Construction - B2B. They design and build high-rise buildings, hotels, and other commercial projects.
Size (Annual Revenue):    $6 million to $25 million
Number of Employees:    11 to 20 employees. 20.
Number of Users:    2 to 5 users. 5.
 
Project & Requirements Overview
Applications needed:    Sales Automation and Marketing Automation
Key features needed:    She wants to be able to track sales, log interaction notes, file documents, schedule reminders/follow-ups, monitor the sales pipeline, send emails/newsletters, track clients/leads, have mobile access, and have quality reporting/analytics. This buyer had specific questions about being able to use Dropbox into the system, have an activity stream team view, and if the system would allow them to upload documents to a client file.
Deployment:    Web-based
Currently using:    Outlook.
Reasons for shopping:    They want a system in place to better manage the sales process and get more organized.
Who they've evaluated:    Acculink and Salesforce.
Price expectations:    Ok up to $60/user/month plus setup fee.
Timeframe:    Immediate.
 
Next Steps
Request:    Demo
Product:    Cosential
Follow-up instructions:    She is hit-or-miss, but available between 9am-5pm EST.
Qualified By:    Paul

column35:
Mainly wants to be able to track and manage opps/leads. Looking for something very basic and easy to use. Viewpoint and bid to win user. Not a fan of SF. 100 year old company. $450 million. He's the new BD and they've never had someone in that role before. Bring him a long slowly. Do not overwhelm.

BD Path – New for Ragner

100 yr old company. 

They done it this way for a long time.

 

Single family ownership. 

 

State and public work historically – always on the bid list. 

 

Moving into more private work. 

 

Engineering

 

VP and Procore

 

Bid2Win for bidding.

 

If cosnetial is going to work for us… 

 

Simple, easy, adoption.

 

Not an accountability whip, but we need to gather data.

 

Whats in the pipe and how reliable is it?

 

Never considered a process.

 

Lets do a demo for Marc first.  Get his feedback.

 

10th of March for group demo. 

 

Next week Mondayy, Tuesday, Wed Morn, Wed late – THURS is BAD. 

 

Parent William Charles – Ragner Benson is a subsidiary…

 

William Charles – Road building, Quarry’s, close to home projects.

 

Ragner Benson side – 2 groups – Civil – National Civil COnst – Site work and Earth works  Industrial.

Vertical construction group.

 

Ragner started in the road and asphalt side, but then went to Vertical construction.  Downtown elevated Rail projects,

 

Civil – Rail (class one and commuter) Environmental Mediation, power and industrial

Building Group – Off to the side.

 

More traction with Ragner Benson Civil group.  THIS IS OUR GROUP – 160 mil rev per year. 

 

Evertyhthing NEW starts with Ragner benson.

 

Same people would decide on William Charles.

 

Ragner Benson Buildings – move to their own beat, but they resist most things…  prob wont want CRM.  Represent 15% of our rev – the website does a poor job of

column35:
Web search – CRM that’s oriented to projects. 

 

Your lead process –

Get a lead , do a proposal.  Send the plans.

 

What kind of info do you have in your proposals. 

 

Materials.  Sq footage, price.  Labor, payment.  Quote not a proposal. 

 

Hardwood floor installers.

Quickbooks.  Likely too small. 

We are very small.  7 ppl.

Changing our business model.  Getting bigger, working closer with businesses.  We are expanding and hard to keep track of the info.  Give the installers the tools to find more business.  Using it from the field.  Keep track of the emails. 

 

Change orders.  Painful.  Need to change real time from the field.  Keep everybody on the same page.  Calendar of our projects.  What projects are coming up on what size and schedule?  Need to allocate people. 

My boss suggesting that we can use a system. 

We work with paper notes and reminders.  Stuff gets lost.  Overlooked. 

His job is to get the plans and come up with sq footage and respond to proposal and track the acceptance of that proposal.  Then we have to invoice the materials at 50%.  Need to get that money received and schedule the job.  Then prior to starting installation, we require the next 50% of material.  We go and install.  Then they pay the final balance.  Needs workflow. 

 

Demo – This week.  

 

 

Event Type: demo
Company: Naples Flooring Company
FullName: Alex Ledesma
Email: naplesflooring@gmail.com
Phone: 2392771213
FormURL: http://www.cosential.com/demo/

column35:
Notes from Demo - 

Past client

How is everything displayed on mobile app?

Can I view all people connected to opportunity on mobile app?

I want!!

Does driving directions integrate with your car GPS?

Mobile note taking important via voice command. Solved every problem she had. She would use all of that.

Business card scanner light interest.  

How can we contact people for an event? Perfect with the ability to log and auto updated based on response i.e accepted/declined etc.

Go/No Go - Probabilities to determine marketing/biz dev efforts

"Very organized and powerful. You get out of it what you put into it."

Implementation - fundamentals are already here. We know your business.

"Not reinventing the wheel right now". Efficiency 

What do we need to chase after? Good method for scoring and ranking using past data. Go/No GO

Dedicated BD folks. Need more dooer/seller

Tracking RFP important

 

Disc Call Notes - 

Carissa is driving in the rain. 

 

Mobile ap is VERY important. 

My company had used Cosential 5 years ago before I was part of it. 

They killed it bc they lost their OFA.

I came along and was the sales leader – relationship leader.  Getting into new markets.  Utilized outlook business contact manager.  Has manipulated it a lot. 

Lots of time on the road.  Has to sit in her office

May be others – my assistant. He has a lot of responsibilities.

Another office 3 hours away.  The VP is doing some sales. 

She does the proposals too.  Estimating puts the numbers. 

Goes back to the office to discuss proposals. 

Contact manager sits on Outlook.

For the sake of argument – tracking info on jobs. 

100 yr old company.

Accubuild – Accounting software

Monday at 9 am. Demo - focus on CRM and Mobile - still show the prop automation stuff just to plant the seed.

column35:
We heard about it last year, watched a couple webinars.  Now its better timing.

 

Already use Dynamix – implemented in early 2013.   Looking to replace.

 

Everyone feels like we aren’t using it to our potential.

 

Square peg, round hole. 

 

Marketing Manager – been here 10 years.  Used to sales support – doing proposals.

 

Involved in the Dynamix implementation. 

 

Selfishly excited about Proposal stuff. 

 

2 ppl doing it now,

 

Axs db trying to track processes. 

 

Sales team needs to focus on the CRM stuff. 

 

Old process – Salesman fills out estimating request form, goes to Gina and to the estimator, Handwritten notes, Monday meeting, Monday meeting.

 

Dynamix helped this process a bit…

 

Stages, go no go, better with Dynamix.

 

What jobs are in estimating dept now and what are those due dates.  See bottlenecks. 

 

Big Construction – Pre-Con managers – degreed engineers.  Source the project and stay with it.  Design phase only.  – 4 of them.  Heavy in design build – in house engineers. 

 

Special Project side – stay with it through the full build.   – Client Reps – 6 – under a million bucks or small quick things. 

 

2 in marketing – her peer does the proposals. 

 

Just implemented an LMS system.

 

Big picture. 

 

Implemented Viewpoint – Went live January of ‘15. 

 

Some ppl love it, some wish they had TCMS. 

 

We asked some marketing peers – JE Dunn – Told us Cosential. 

 

IT Manager watched the webinar.  Says he is skeptical Inbounds.

 

Requirements –

 

  1. MS 365 hosted exchange.  – can we integrate.

 

  1. Cell phones and sync.  

 

I had put their opp in nuture from lack of response, but she emailed saying they are almost ready for a demo.  Asked for a recorded PA webinar first.

column35:
Aussie

 

Referred to us by a review page.  Software Advice.

 

I understanding. 

 

Situation is – We already have a PM software.  Spectrum.  Accounting and PM. 

 

What we need is the CRM.  And database for your clientele. 

 

Jason is the Biz Dev Director – Sales responsibilities. 

 

Jason does the proposals as well.  Coordinates with other.

 

His role is to make the intro – depending on the project type, the relationship will be managed by different people.

Office 365. 

 

Has used CRM for a long time – former recruiter.

 

Live demo and costs. – 5 users likely.  Jason will be the power user.

Wants to move.

column35:
Formerly US Engineer Company – implemented Cosential while I was there.  Helped implement and used heavily

With US Eng Through June of 15.

Joined Raceline in August – BD Manager – call on the big companies – tracking down projects

Engieering, fabrication

250 mi rev

2 business units

Biz unit 1 - manufacturing – can manufacturer.  Our company built the plant that made your can.  – pretty small industry and they know who is who – don’t think they need CRM.  The sharepoint solution was a driver b/c it was very cheap and was supposed to get them off of spreadsheets.

Biz unit 2 - process and energy group = this is Petes group – fairly new – new people - 5 ppl - Pete (BD), John(manager of biz unit), Miranda (Cosnetial potential OFA and group admin) Joe (BD) and Rob (BD)  All 5 would be full users.  

Guy who was supposed build the Sharepoint stuff has spit.  Project bombed.  Never paid him so nothing lost but time.  alot of time.  

Pete told the owner that he used Cosneital and that it was awesome.  Liked the concept but couldn’t sell the Can side on the idea of a more expensive crm.

"No way that sharepoint can get close to what you do"

So now boss has given the green light to look at us.  Spend a little money. 

Gonna look at other options but heavily favoring Cosential due to past use. 

Can Biz unit guys may be on board from day one due to the sharepoint fiasco but in the past said they didnt want to spend real money. 

Pete is using outlook only for his current d2d activities.

 

Pete - Really liked the pipeline and opp management.

 

Opp projects to real bids. - performance reporting

 

Managing a dozen projects now and has no idea how they are progressing.

 

No proposal automation upfront - may want to plant the seed.  

 

Raceline should be a good fit for proposal automation.  Lots of very similar proposals. Gaining pete's interest.

Pete wants to help us sell John.

US Eng was using pipeline data for forecasting.  CFO has a program he uses for forecasting, wins and losses.  Excel or access.

Accounting software – not sure.  Part of the reason they balked at Cosential. - didnt want crm data flowing into acct system.  I explained how it works.  

Send Proposal info – build a plan with Pete to show John pricing and implementation timeline. 

John would then try to sell it to the can side.

Show some cool sample reports.  Forecasting up to the main office.  How far forward looking?  For the year or more.  Bi weekly activity report – opps and current opp status. 

Pete will send me the report – and we will show John how to do it in Cosneital.

Number of Employees:    101 to 500 employees. 200-300 employees.

Project & Requirements Overview
Applications needed:    Sales Automation
Key features needed:    They need to track their customers/clients and the projects and accounts associated with those clients. They need the system to handle interaction tracking, follow-up reminders, and in-depth client information.
Deployment:    Web-based
Currently using:    SharePoint.
Reasons for shopping:    The system is cheap and not a good fit for their company.
Who they've evaluated:    SharePoint.

column35:
Hi Ron,

 

I thought it might be helpful to outline where we are with Deltek and some challenges, for our meeting on Thursday.

 

CRM – Current State

Today, we use Deltek’s Vision database and product as the foundation of our CRM architecture.  Our Business Development process is designed around an account management framework.  In construction, the real, total lifecycle of any given pursuit can last 5 years.  We are often aware of opportunities 2 years prior to their going to market for bid.  Some bid processes can run up to 1 year.  Finally, project delivery can last from 1-4 years.   Therefore, our CRM tool has evolved to help manage the following:

 

-        Account/Customer management

-        Pursuit/Opportunity tracking/management  (leads)

-        Forecasting (3 year sales outlook)

-        Pursuit Management (4 phases, proposals, team assignments)

-        Partial Talent Database

o   Data base linking each employee to prior projects, skill sets, qualifications

-        Project Award Management (job creation)

 

Today, the system is mostly available as an online data base.  We have implemented their mobile application.  Report writing and analysis often has to be completed using other 3rd party tools.  We have about 120 total users broken down as follows:  40 account managers, 12 marketing specialists, 30 profit center level users, 40 administrative users including accounting, compliance/legal, HR, and others.

 

CRM – Desired Future State

 

We are currently in the process of reviewing the Deltek product to make a decision on either staying with the product or migrating to a different platform.  Below are the issues driving this review:

 

-        The need for better data analytics

-        The need for stronger report writing and dashboard capabilities

-        The need for simpler data interface and user input, including mobile capabilities

-        The ability for 1 CRM product to manage all of the current state functions

-        The ability to integrate data across systems (CRM, Accounting (J.D. Edwards) and Industry Specific Project Management Software (Prolog)

-        The best value solution – capability x cost

 

Our current system does some of these well, and others not so well.

 

Thanks

Mary

column35:
7/08/15 - Zach emailed me this morning- he is ready to revisit Cosential, we're coordinating a call for later today.

2/24 - tt Zach.  Just moved offices, has not been focused on CRM.  Still very early in looking at what is out there.Thinks he probably needs to try using Act a bit (which apparently they have) to get a sense of how a CRM could fit his workflow, then start to explore options.  I encouraged him to attend the webinar next week.  Closing lead - he isn't moving on anything any time soon.1/19 - emailed webinar links, encouraged him to attend proposal automation on wednesday 

1/15- lvm & emailed Zach, we touche base this afternoon.  Very eary stages of looking for CRM - probably not a fit at this point, but maybe - Zach is the only guy toing BD & marketing.  REcognized he'll need to get more sophisticated at some point, but not looking to pull trigger anytime soon - this is more exploring options and pricing.  Encouraged him to attend public webinars, let me know if that looks appealing enough to evaluate in depth.

column35:
8/31 - Not selecting Cosential - are going with Project-SalesAchiever for two primary reasons:  very inexpensive, and enables them to generate work orders/bids.  

6/10 - detailed Q&A w/ Carole:  Refs (not yet), Training, tech specs, etc.  Scheduling another call for deeper dive into outlook & proposal automation

6/09 - tt Carol - she thought she had sent me an email recapping her partners meeting, but hadn't.  She is going to email me proposed next steps, would like to discuss after I've had a chance to look at that.

5/29 - intro/qualification call w/ Carol early this afternoon, then demo late this afternoon.  She is meeting w/ partners on Monday, will include Cosential on her short list of 2-3 possible solutions, likely demo w/ partners coming up next, check in w/ her Monday afternoon or Tuesday.   Demo notes: She likes resume generation capabilities.  Wants Cosential publishing engine to replace their estimating/quote forms.  Since Publisher 4.0 does not pull from Opportunity records, that isn't a good use case for Cosential.  She thinks it is too daunting to ask partners/engineers to input or paste 3-4 data points from that form (client, fee, description/scope of work, possibly date sent) into Cosential. Ideally, wants them to only type the information ONCE, in Cosential.  Then the quote form could be generated automatically.  Currently, that information is not documented ANYwhere - no central repository of information, no way to know what quotes have been sent out, nothing.  Individual engineers MAY keep a log of what they've sent out, maybe not, nobody knows.  She wants it all visible to everyone, but does not want to add any additional keystrokes over current processes... a little bit unrealistic.  Despite all that, she thinks Cosential could be a big help to them.  She has been copying their resume information (name of client, description of project) into an Access database to prepare for upload to another system.

3/18 - intro call w/ Casey, qualified Opp, decision likely Q2.  Firm-wide initiative.  Currently:  Excel for Opps, Clearview accounting, NuForma PM, proprietary marketing database, no CRM.  Some Outlook, some other contact mgmt/email programs in place.  Casey has used Deltek Vision in the past, discussed differences.  Pricing, likely $3100-ish on implementation w/ no FDC (proposal automation probably not something they want inititially).  180 employees, 2 offices: HQ in NYC w/ a new 6-person office in Shanghai.  Targeting 20 users: entire marketing dept. + 12 partners.  Demo at 10:30 CDT on Thursday, 3/19.  Casey has done her homework and talked w/ several other CRM vendors, including Salesforce and some add-on module from Clearview.  Susan Strauss, Associate Partner and Director of Marketing and Communication, will also be on demo.

3/18 - demo of proposal automation for Ruben, James, and team.  Talked w/ Ruben later - we can do Access integration for $2500, but it isn't something they need initially.  Want to start smaller - only 3 users - then likely to expand as they get a better handle on which roles really benefit from Cosential.  Generated new agreement, sent to Ruben along w/ invoice, James will likely cut a paper check, signature today or tomorrow.

3/11 - They've discussed internally, after seeing the webinar, and would like a proposal.  Wants to see 3/18 webinar, but they fully anticipate signing agreement immediately thereafter.  Got some detail on current data sources - 3k+ records in Access database, contacts in both Access and Outlooks, a couple of spreadsheets.  No FDC, want proposal for 9 users.  Emailed agreement to Ruben & James.

3/06 - Ruben emailed questions, I answered, prposped w talk monday

3/03 - inbound on sales line.  Looking for CRM, demo'd SFDC, did not like it.  Environmental Engineering firm, primarily phase 1 env. site assessments.  Hard bid - put together about 200 proposals/month, win 80-150.  5 people in sales, looking for 5-10 users.  Have a homegrown Access database, connected to the web, which automates some of their proposal/bid functions.  May be able to connect to it w/ our API, but that would likely be down the road a bit.  Quickbooks for accounting.  Qualified on price (approx. $3k implementation).  Needs:  contact/interaction management, ability to classify people/roles on pursuits.  James would sign check, but will ask Morgan (a she), one of his salespeople, to be point person on eval.  Sending link to Wednesday webinar, Morgan will attend, we'll like schedule a demo after that.  Sent my contact info, webinar links.

column35:
3/06 - emailed Paige, propose demo times Tuesday and intro call times today.  Had intro call:  12-person firm. Growing.  Quickbooks accounting.  Need contact mgmt, pipeline mgmt, proposal automation.  Discussed pricing & implementation (approx. $3k).  Paige only one doing proposals/quals, nobody else can find relevant info easily (was an issue when she was on maternity leave).  Use outlook for contacts.  Have a central "jobs spreadsheet" with all Opportunity information:  fees, contract value, probability. Managing partner goes through that to determine macklog.  Also helpful:  photo storage (create slide shows for recruiting events), mailing lists, see references.  Pain points:  things get lost, unable to find info they need in a timely fashion, no formal processes.  Demo next week:  start w/ CRM overview/terminology.  Realistically, they would probably want to roll something out in late summer or fall, but TBD.  
 

wants a demo next week - see her email to me below - JH

 

 

I had a Cosential sales representative provide a demo of the software several years ago. I am interested in seeing if I can get a demo scheduled for next week so that our other company partners can see what the software can do. We have a partners meeting and ideally I’d like to have a demo at some point during our meeting. Is there anyone available to provide us an online demo of the software next Tuesday, March 10th? Please let me know as soon as possible.

 

Thank you,

 

 

Paige Viehouser, Principal

CPSM | LEED Green Associate

column35:
4/1 - Athena reports they are planning to sign within the next 30 days, as soon as they have launched their new website.  Asked for references, I'll get to work on that for her.

3/19 - lvm for Athena

3/18 - lvm athena

3/06 - got some insight from Athena before our demo. demo w/ Cory & Athena - kept it brief, Cory was pressed for time, focused primarily on contact management - contact detail, contact grid, call log, some dashboard widgets.  Cory gave positive feedback, which was great - his stance on our intro call earlier this week was a lot more challenging, and I wasn't convinced he was fully invested in the evaluation until the demo today.  Talked w/ Athena afterwards - she wants this done ASAP.  She, Cory, and Sean (other partner) will meet week of March 16th (there is some travel, OOO prior to them), which should prompt a quick decision... Athena confident that we'll have a contract in place before EOM - she has already primed Sean, they are not looking at any other solutions, they all understand the need to get something off the ground.  Sending her registration info for the 3/18 webinar on proposal automation, we'll talk that week.  

 3/02 - intro call w/ Cory.  Wants to demo.  Views Cosential as something they will grow into a bit, but necessary given their rate of growth.  Demo Friday, 11 am CST.

Athena called in on sales line - heard about Cosential from Katherine Spurlock of Charles Salter & Associates, who raved about us.  SMall firm, no CRM, Axium Ajera accounting, all info on pursuits lives in the head of Corey, one of the partners, who does the bulk of BD work.  Other partner (Shawn?) starting to do some BD.  Athena wears a lot of hats, helps Corey.  Use Google Drive, Google email, Google contacts.  No visibility, transparency, or pipeline management.  Corey has a drawer full of business cards from people he has met at conferences.  Minimal data migration needs, would want three users at most.  Ballpark $4500-$5500 first-year spend.  Firm is prime on all projects, subcontracts are paid by Axis.  Growing, recognize that current processes won't scale. Athena will chat with Corey, if he is amenable, we'll schedule an intro call with him, possibly straight to full demo if he is on board conceptually and comfortable with price.  Sent Athena my contact info, she is talking w/ Corey on 2/26 and will let me know how we proceed.

4/14 - tt Kate - she sat with David as he e-signed it last week, but she's happy to do it again.  He'll be in the office this afternoon, she'll tag up with him and re-sign.  Check is on its way to us right now.  Re-sent agreement to Kate & David. 

4/13 - apparently signature did not come through on echosign, emailed Kate.  LVM for her later in day - just need them to re-do echosign signature.

4/09 - signed agreement in, Brett sent invoice to david.  I forwarded that along to Kate, as well, who reiterated that she will remain primary point of contact & OFA. 

4/08  Lvm Kate.  David Lambertsen called later in the day, we went through one quick redline on agreement, I generated new version and sent it over to him, should have signature tomorrow morning.  Check will be cut within 3 business days or so.

3/19 - tt Kate, they will ask Jim Viner for final approval in Monday morning meeting.  ref conversations have been awesome, she has a call scheduled w/ Theresa and Rakhul that hasn't happened yet, but everyone has been positive - Adam Lemoine was especially helpful, Nancy was wowed on that call, and Adam offered to offer them guidance going forward, which they appreciate.  I reminded her that Anthony Chiaradonna has not been contacted yet, she is going to get on that - Kathy is the one who requested it.  Will ask Jim to sign off in Monday morning meeting.  Revised seat count - only four - I'll generate new version of agreement.

3/09+ - tt Jim Viner, President - wants more refs, not just Timberline (which makes things easier for me) - will get more today.  Intro through Kate.

3/04 - intro'd kathy, glen, and joe to Consigli CIO anthony chiaradonna

2/26 - Intro'd kate to Anthony at Consigli.  Working on other refs.   emails w/ Kate, Jim is OOO today and tomorrow.  Won't get it done this week.  Wants more references, too.  Good on five users, sent her agreement for that.

2/25 - traded emails w/ Kate, scheduled call for 3:40 pm today.  call w/ KAte - several questions raised in internal meeting.  I was able to address most (they're things we've covered before), but a sticking point:  ...they talked with someone who had left Cosential for MS Dynamics - I don't know name of firm.  That has given them pause, and they now want to speak with MULTIPLE contacts who use FDC/CDC for Timberline.  Possibility of close this week, but not a guarantee.  Still focused on five licenses, but haven't determined that definitively.

2/18 - traded emails w/ Kate, talked strategy before demo.  President (Jim) and BD Director (David) will be key players on demo, also Joe in IT.  Focus on high-level stuff, not too much detail.  Dynamics is coming in at a higher cost, only big appeal with them is tighter Outlook integration.  Had demo - nearly 2 hours again - went very well.  Lots of great, engaged questions.  After call, sent FDC info to Kate - Kathy & Joe wanted to review.  Kate emailed back - feedback really positive, should be a "yes", pending IT's take on FDC.  

2/17 - email exchange w/ Kate, booked 2nd demo for next week, will include president.

2/12- Good demo w/ Kate, Wendy (marketing), Kathy (IT + President's assistant), and Nancy (BD).  2 hours, they really liked it.  Between us and Dynamics.

2/10 - Kate called in on sales line, good introductory call.  80-ish in-office employees.  Doing everything on an "unbelieveable" number of different spreadsheets now.  Outlook, Timberline.  Would want five users initially, possibility of scaling it up to Project Managers down the road.  Approx. $9200 first-year spend, including implementation + Timberline FDC - price not a problem.  Kate is driver/influencer, president is financial decision-maker.  Scheduled demo for 9:30 am CST on Thursday, 2/12.

3/19 - talked w/ 2 references, intro'd to Brett.  He called me back, has approval, he'll connect w/ refs, should get agreement inked by early next week at latest. They probably won't want to kick implementation off in earnest until mid to late april, I'm re-generating agreement w/ 6/1/15 anniversary to expedite signature.  He mostly wants to talk w/ refs to get advice on how to prepare for implementation (data cleanup, etc.).  Sending updated agreement.

3/03 - traded emails w/ Brett- Andrea Rome is new Business Administrator, Brett has requested one more demo, we're aiming for Tuesday, 3/10.  - confirmed 11 am cst on 3/10. Andrea's email:  arome@mdpeg.com

2/18- He started at MDP this month.  Mostly doing RFP responses, fairly quick turnaround.  Not an easy process - spends a ton of time searching for similar projects to highlight, similar cover letters and resumes so he doesn't have to reinvent the wheel.  He is focused on proposal automation only, not BD stuff, so that was our focus.  Using Word primarily, has InDesign but not using it much yet.  Loved proposal automation, things this is ideal fit.  Said he thought evaluation process slowed down over last couple of months because they were waiting to fill his role.  He'll need to talk it over w/ Pam, who is only in the office on Tuesdays and Wednesdays at this point (and will be OOO all next week), they may need to get President to approve spend.  Please call first week of March, but he is very positive about moving this forward quickly.  Ajera FDC, 3 users, total $6370.

11/19 -  good demo, would likely want minimum rollout.  Potential Cosential users at MDP: Pam, Michael Passas (president/principal), Anglea (office manager, primary Ajera user)

10/21 - Pam called in on sales line.  Using Ajera Complete 8.0.  Likes notion of FDC.  No current CRM.  Minimum rollout ($2160), implementation $4200.  Very few RFP responses, lots of word doc proposals generated quickly.  Bulk of project info in Ajera, they've been using it for a year.  Emailed Pam, likely demo once she discusses this internally.  Unsure of timeframe - probably very quickly if $6360 startup cost is not an issue.

4/1 -   TT Robin, sent updated agreement, asked her to have John call me - she suspects it is for some kind of budget reason he doesn't want to sign until next week, but not sure.  He has been in and out office all day.

LVM John, will try you later this afternoon if I don't hear back.

3/31 - Emails w/ Robin over last 2 days, she wants an agreement for signature April 6th.  I've been trying this week to understand why they don't want to sign right away, haven't been able to get an answer or catch either Robin or John on the phone.  Does he not want to pay until April?  We can work around that.

3/19-- emailed robin 

3/05 - Emails w/ Robin - she talked w/ John, still want to do this, we'll get re-engaged later in March.

2/25 - talked w/ Robin - slammed w/ proposals, very busy. Cosential in budget for this quarter, Robin expects to lock this up early to mid March. She is "past ready to move forward", she just needs time to get with John and have him sign off, please call next week, she will have had a chance to talk with John by then.

2/20 - email to robin - ready to get this off the ground?

1/14- Robin emailed me:  got buried under projects. they got swamped at end of year and are underwater right now, that's why John didn't get it done at EOY and has been tough to get ahold of.  Still going to do it, but January is a long shot.  Robin said it will get done this quarter.  Moved close date out to March.

1/13 - lvm Robin - insight on John? Haven't been able to reach him since our last convo at end of year

12/29 convo w/ John, getting signature this month, pay by check January

12/08 - tt Robin, would like to remove Ajera connector from agreement.  Want to start implementation in January, should be able to get contract executed this month - I'll send an updated agreement w/ an incentive.

11/18- Robin called, they'd like to do this:  3 full, 9 read-only, Ajera FDC.  Not sure if they will kick it off right away or first of the year - I offered 2/1/16 anniversary date in exchange for executing agreement before Thanksgiving.  Sent agreement.

9/18 - Demo w/ Robin and John Davenport

9/09 - Lauren Kendle at Axium intro'd me to Robin Buchanan, who is interested in evaluting Cosential

column35:
4/13 - emailed Linda - quick conversation to walk through agreement?  Linda replied - she was out of the office all of last week, we'll talk between 9 and 10 tomorrow.

4/06 - Linda unsure of where all necessary docs are (MSA, signature page), LVM explaining links on document and asked her to call me to help walk her through

4/02 - agreement to Linda

3/11 - tt Linda, CEO & CFO attended viewpoint webinar, seemed positive.  They are going to discuss at their management mtg on Monday.  Talked through details of implementation and pricing ($5610 imp. fee w/ Viewpoint FDC).  I'm going to put a pricing proposal together for her to take into the Monday morning, meeting, 9 full + 2 R-O.  They may ultimately want fewer seats, but that's what they're thinking at the moment. She knows I'm OOO Friday and Monday, we'll talk on tuesday of next week.

3/09 - called Linda to let her know Viewpoint is hosting a webinar to highlight new integration capabilities w/ COsentia.  She was made aware of that webinar today, they are attending!  They're finishing up audit right now, will be ready to re-engage on Cosential once that is finished.

  Please call her early next week.

2/20 - emailed Linda re: reconvene.  Also let her know we're close to completing 2-way sync w/ viewpoint.

1/21 - traded emails w/ Linda - she clarified that Q2 is their likely timeframe for implementing Cosential.  

1/13-  Linda reports that they are still interested, but very busy and she won't be able to reconnect until early February.  I asked for a quick update on timing and whether Cosential is firm choice for their firm. 

1/12/15- emailed to Linda (haven't received update from them since November) re: status of eval, move this along?

11/10 - Good demo:  Michael (Mike) Grier - Pres. & CEO; Lynn Anderson - VP Pre-Construction Svcs; Linda Walton - Sec./Treas.; Karman Diehl - VP HR; Kurt Grier - Exec. VP; Adam Dunn - CFO; Larry Weiss - Ops.  45-50 in-office employees. Use InDesign for proposals.  Do a lot of AIA form 305 for quals.  Talked pricing, implementation details.  $5700-ish on implementation, including Viewpoint.  They had questions on # of customers, # that use Viewpoint, # that are in Construction, etc.  Details on Viewpoint Connector.  Jed to email them some info on what happens to our FDC when Viewpoint updates (talked through it, but I'd like to confirm).  They are discussing internally, check in w/ Linda later this week.

10/16 - intro call w/ Linda, went well.  Use Act! and Timberline. Demo scheduled for November.

10/06 - talked w/ KArman, who referred me to two other people in the firm.  Karman passed along Cosential info, and my name, to the two people in her firm who are interested in pulling project info from Viewpoint and using it to complete proposals in InDesign - that is not part of Karman's role.  Linda Walton, the Corporate Secretary/Treasurer, and Michael Grier, President, are the two interested in talking with me.  Emailed Karman my contact info, I should hear from Linda and/or Michael relatively soon.

9/29 - lvm Karman

Viewpoint Conference-Jed

column34: 6/18 - touch base will Pat this month.  If no progress/timetable in June, move this into nurture.
column35:
5/27 - finally connected w/ Pat - no progress. They have Ajera accounting (not sure if on-premise or cloud), and have learned about Ajera CRM, so will have to look at that before pulling trigger on anything.  No firm timetable... they do not move quickly... partners will have to approve decision/spend, and partners seem to meet infrequently.  Stay in touch w/ Pat.

2/19- Partners have not met.  Pushing Opp into March.  Partners are supposed to have a weekly meeting every Friday, but the last few months have been waaay off.  Holidays, snowstorms, travel - they have hit one of the last 8 scheduled meetings.  Until they actually sit down and discuss, this will not move forward.  Pat will keep me posted, and she continues to push on her end, but she has not been able to corral them.  

2/06- Per Pat, still trying to get them to meet, will let me know.

1/28 - tt Pat, partners not meeting this week, thanks in part to NYC snowstorm, she won't be able to get them to meet until next week, moving opp to Feb

1/23 - emailed pat- updates? she replied, trouble corralling the partners.  She said "This has been my problem.  But I am working on it.".  

1/19 - emailed Pat - have leaders met?  also included draft implementation timeline.
1/15- lvm & emailed to check on status - have they met today?
1/08 - leadership is meeting next week, we should be able to get this done then.  Pat said initial cash outlay may be tricky - they're waiting to get paid on some stuff - but if we can split this into two payments, then we can get it done in January.  Connect at the end of next week after meeting, should be able to move things forward then if their leadership doesn't flake on meeting - apparently last scheduled meeting or two was pushed out because key people were on holiday vacations, now everyone is back in office.

 

 

12/18 - contract to pat - 2 versions, w/ ajera and w/o

 

 

 

10/06 - traded emails w/ Pat - has not talked w/ partners yet (out for jewish holidays last week), check back on Monday

10/03 - lvm for Pat

9/17 - Intro call w/ Pat - she likes Cosential... a Cosential customer called V-J (?) rents space from them, Pat sits right next to Sharon the Cosential OFA, so she has seen and heard good things about us.  Pat has an MBA in IT... lots of database experience.  Spent the summer having an intern put a lot of their info into spreadsheets, they know they need a database.  Use Ajera (v. 7.9xxxx).  Pricing:  $2160 min, approx. $3100 standard implementation, +$1000 for Ajera FDC.  Pat handles all marketing and biz dev.  Users would be Pat, a Marketing Coordinator, and maybe one partner.  A couple of other partners may want read-only.  Discussed implementation in detail.  $$ a concern.  Cindy Feinberg is majority partner, she is hearing good things about Cosential, open to idea of investing in CRM database.  One other partner is "old and stubborn" and had a "nightmare" Cosential implementation years ago at another firm (volume of data was problem), so he may be a roadblock.  Jed to send overview info to Pat, she is going to tag up with Cindy sometime in the next few days - that should give Pat a better understanding of possible timing (between now and December?  early 2015?).  Jed to call Pat mid-to-late next week if I haven't heard from her by then. 

 

 

9/16 - emailed

 

 

CRM Survey - No CRM but open to being contacted

11/24 - pushing to December, per convo w/ Kellie

10/08 - good demo w/ Mike Karvakko & Kellie - sending proposal, October start

9/12 -  tt Kellie - folks have been busy w/ other things, still reviewing internally.  Call in 2 weeks to discuss how to proceed - likely demo for firm principal.

9/03 - Talked w/ Kellie - she has shared info/thoughts on Cosential internally, other parties are reviewing and she will have feedback/interest level from everyone later this week.  Assuming the firm principal is on board, likely next step is demo for him.  She should have info by Friday.  Call her on Monday if I haven't heard anything by then.

8/19 -Good demo.  Qualified on price.  Kellie had some experience using Zoho in the past, primarily just as contact/scheduling/call logging database.  Kellie thinks Cosential is the right fit - it can handle all functions that they need, currently managed by four or five different & unconnected systems/files, all in one place.  She said they are planning to buy an architecture firm - could we do something to separate those two businesses within Cosential?  Yes - firm org.  Sending overview info, she will be sharing it with team, we'll reconvene on Tuesday, 9/02 to plan next steps - likely 2nd demo for firm principal is next. 

8/19 - Comments: Ajera Customer. 5 Users. Looked a number of solutions. 1-2 months.Good lead. 
Talked w/ Kellie, scheduled 2pm demo today.  Her role is Marketing Manager.  Firm principal would be involved in decision - firm-wide initiative to find CRM system - but principal will not be on demo today.  4PMs and principal doing biz dev, "everyone is doing their own thing" when it comes to tracking pursuits - individual spreadsheets, etc.  Interested in both CRM & proposal automation.  Kellie does proposals "manually", uses InDesign.  23 in-office employees.

column35:
8/21- SPoke w/ Brittany, they are going to go with a CRM system called "Leadmaster".  She did not elaborate, only said it was right fit for them.  I suspect that is based on price/contract (pay-as-you-go for Leadmaster) and fact that Landmark is starting with the Real Estate group only, would add construction/development group to CRM only at an as-yet-unspecified later date.  Per my intro call with Brittany, Cosential is a great fit for construction/development group, but multiple systems could give them the very basic contact management functionality they want for Real Estate Group. (principal wants system that shows him which properties are rented, which are vacant, and when the vacant ones will be rented).  

8/14 - Intro call w/ Brittany:  demo tomorrow w/ Brittany and Ryan (Biz Dev, "in the trenches" perspective).  Decision will be up to Anthony, president, out of office this week.  He has instructed Brittany to bring him the best CRM solution.  Have Dynamics currently, a years-old on-premise instance, which isn't working and nobody is using it.  63 people in firm.  Two sides to business:  Development (hired by hospital, lease their land, construct buildings for them, then lease those to hospital), and Tenant Development (basically, specialized Commercial realty - leasing spaces they already own to doctors and hospitals... also do some property management on those spaces).  Want to start with Tenant Development side (6 people in BD/mktg), but get everyone on same system eventually (possibly up to 40 people, although I doubt all would be full).  Develpment side is the one that needs Project-focused CRM, Tentant side really doesn't.  Brittany understands all of this.  Price:  $4320 for six users, plus implementation (ballpark $3100, not including Timberline FDC).  Demo tomorrow, then we'll present to Anthony.

column35:
1/23 - good convo w/ Kristen and Kara, they are going w/ Cosential and we'll get this kicked off asap - updating dates on contract, Kristen will take to CFO Judd for signature on Monday.  

1/21 - traded emails w/ Kristen, set up call for Friday, 2 pm CST

1/14 - lvm again for Kristen, will continue to try to catch her - last update in December was they want to get this going first of the year

9/15 - email from Kristen on Friday - timeline change - likely Q4 (to be up and running in January).  They're relocating the office in September.  

9/09- demo for team.  

9/05 - scheduled demo for 9/09 at 2:30 CDT - entire team

8/22 - great demo w/ Kristen, James, and Kara.  Ideal fit for what they need - very impressed.  Small initial rollout (3 full, 4 R-O), likely to expand within first year to 4 full, 10-12 R-O.  Implementation:  $5610, including Timberline.  Sending proposal, some implementation overview info to Kristen.  Would like to get ASAP, will likely need to get approval on spend - that may mean one more demo for some of the Operations department. Kristen hopes to have some clarity on Monday.  Only potential obstacle is budget - Kristen spent about $7k getting an in-house system built, and it does not do everything they need it to... they wish they would have found Cosential before making that investment.  James thinks the business case for Cosential will be compelling.  CFO will like Timberline sync, which bodes well for his approval on spend.

8/14 - traded emails w/ Kristen, scheduled demo for Friday, 8/22 at 12 CDT.  James McFarlane (VP Biz Dev) and Kara Soriano (mktg).  

8/13 - emailed to schedule intro call, had that today:  50-person construction firm, 6 yrs old, rapid growth.  Timberline accounting.   Kristen spent approx. $8k to have someone build their own (web/cloud-based) project database, now wants something better...  talked through pricing ($3100-$6k implementation, $2500 of which is Timberline).  Her focus is marketing - very detailed questions on our capabilities.  Have about 50 fields in project db. Scheduling demo with Kristen, BD person, and other marketing person.  If that goes well, we'll demo for firm leadership.  Likely to implement Q4. She'll email me proposed dates on demo.

column35:
Please followup:

 

Hi Jennifer,

 

Thanks for reaching out. We were in the midst of an office move for the first half of the year, so had to postpone big-ticket conversations. I saw your booth at the SMPS Pacific Regional Conference in Huntington Beach earlier this year, but when I was able to get over to talk to them on the last day, they weren’t at the booth, but it worked out fine, as we had to delay any major purchase conversations until after the office move.

 

We are now looking ahead to 2015 to get some numbers together, and would love to earmark some dollars for a database rollout in 2015. Not sure if you are the correct person to talk to, and if not, please let me know who I should be speaking to. We have been in need of finding a more comprehensive system, one that talks to Outlook (and possibly our other databases), and covers our major needs: CRM, lead tracking, and project database. We are not interested in proposal generator software, so I’m guessing that Cosential would be more in line with what we are seeking as opposed to Axium, but will defer to you.

 

It would be great to have an initial conversation regarding our needs, and then to be able to see a demo of the software, and get a cost estimate of course.

 

Let me know your timing and what additional info you would need from me.

 

Thanks,

Todd

7/17 - demo with Tyler after intro from Lauren Kendle.  Went well - Tyler is familiar w/ Deltek Vision (used to use it), understands CRM systems.  2 offices. Lead tracking, lead generation, content management, database of project info.  Opps/Leads generated through relationships.  Liked proposal automation.  $4200 implementation, $2160 licenses (min) - would likely want only 3 users.  70 people in firm.  InDesign.  Use PCs.  Rarely do SF330s.  Mostly prime.  Tyler also liked reporting - sometimes clients will ask them how much work they have in the pipeline (as a way to determine their availability?? not clear).  She wants to think this over for a day or two, please email her pricing guidance and resources she can look at.  Possible August close - if they go with Cosential, would likely be before end of summer.

Tyler intro'd by Lauren Kendle at Axium

Alyssa Attended PA Webinar 6/18

10/07 - emailed Brent:  decisions?

8/21 - called for Brent, spoke w/Heather, who passed along this msg from Brent:  No decision yet.  He is looking at a couple of other options and "waiting on some other people" (not sure if that means waiting for quotes from other companies, or waiting for people internally to weight in).  Brent will contact me when he has more insight.

8/18 - lvm for Brent 

7/31 - Brent LVM for me - still evaluating a couple of other options on CRM, has not made decision yet.  Hoping to get some clarity within next week or two, will get back to me when he has some insight/update on their decision-making.  

7/29 - lvm w/ recep - please call me today, traveling rest of week

7/28 -lvm w/ recep for Brent

7/24 - lvm, will try again later. Tried again, nm.  Talked w/ Paul @ Axium - he spoke with Coralee (sp?) at Farr West, and apparently Brent has been traveling a lot.  Keep trying

7/23- vm, nm, keep calling 

7/21 - lvm Brent Farr, will try you tomorrow morning.

7/10  - called Brent, no msg (so far).  pinged Paul L. to see if he had heard anything - Paul said demo went over very well; he thinks Brent is completely on board and we can get this closed this within a week (July! Boom!).  Paul scheduled to talk with him tomorrow, will know more then.

7/03 - demo w/ Brent Farr, went well - impressed w/ capabilities.  $4k+ for implementation.  May want to get Cosential for both this company and another, separate entity he owns (Sierra Controls).  Asked for quote for 6 full licenses, sent that today.  We'll touch base next week to talk about next steps.  Using Ajera 7.8 right now, likely moving to Ajera 8 soon.

7/2 - scheduled demo for tomorrow

column34: 6/1/15 - Check in with Chad this summer - things going smoothly with Salesforce?  Interested in revisiting Cosential?
column35:
7/21 - lvm Chad - he called back, couldn't get firm principal to agree to greater spend... wants to spend hundreds, rather than thousands, and want something up and running ASAP.  Cosential Chad's first choice, Tracker his second, but is investing in Salesforce because it is the only thing he can start using TODAY without any configuration.  Please call him in a year - he likes Cosential, might be in a better position to invest down the road.

7/09 - emailed thoughts on boss convo, proposed call today.   Chad emailed back - conference in Florida next week, his superior focused on that.  Planning to address Cosential either during conference or following week when back in office. Replied suggesting we connect when they've talked; perhaps new conference leads would be a good opportunity to look at how Cosential could streamline processes.   

7/07 - Reviewed Cosential w/ Chad, talked through typical CRM evaluation criteria (he's new to CRM evaluation).  He likes our system, but would not use all of its features.  Talked through pricing - we're offering CRM only licenses.  He is not certain that the value of Cosential is $1500+ more than Tracker RMS... or at least not certain the best way to sell that to his boss.  My thoughts on that:  1) Superior Implementation, best practices, "teach a man to fish" (we talked about that); 2) More features (tracking subs, prequals, task assignment, integration of lead sources/web forms - we talked about that); 3) Marketing Functions for the Marketing Department (have not discussed); 4) reporting capabilities for Firm Principal (discussed a little bit on first demo, didn't get into today).  Jed and Chad to reconvene Wednesday to discuss how best to present this to his boss.

7/03 - Chad reports that he has eliminated Salesforce and Sugar from contention, will decide between Cosential and Tracker.  Scheduled call for 11 am CDT on Monday to discuss next steps.  Would like to make a decision by July 11th.  Would still need to get principal to sign off, July deal if we're his choice.

7/02 - demo w/ Chad, went well.  Didn't show projects or proposal automation- those aren't important.  He liked the ability to create/assign tasks, even to those who aren't Cosential end users.  Liked lead management, ability to integrate with web service.  Email to "...@cosential.com" for creating leads through his webform is probably easiest path to get webform leads in place.  Bottom line:  He likes Cosential.  Price ($4200+) too high compared to Tracker RMS (approx. $444/year for one person) - he will not feel confident taking that to firm principal when Tracker gives most of what he is looking for (simplicity, essential functions for tracking/contacts, seemingly good support/implementation).  If we can get more competitive on price, we'll discuss further.  Talked it over with Matt, emailed him offer for $2435 first-year cost (up to 3 CRM-only users, 4 hrs implementation, 3 hrs training... didn't break out the detail, just $2435 first year, $1080 subsequent years).  If that makes us competitive, let's tag up to discuss pricing detail and next steps.  (NOTE:  other systems are letting him "kick the tires" in Sandbox instances, he would have preferred if we could do that, but understands that it isn't an option).

7/01 - intro call, went well - wants a decision quickly.  Price will become an issue, more than likely, but right fit more important than dollars.  Demo tomorrow at 10:30 am CDT

Project & Requirements Overview

Applications needed:

Sales Automation

Key features needed:

He mainly needs a program to track his customers and contacts. Their sales pipeline has new business coming in all the time and their sales team needs a way to manage their customers' information efficiently. The system must me user-friendly and help them save time during the sales process.

Deployment:

Not Determined

Currently using:

He has been using Reed Construction Data and Franklin Covey's Plan Plus.

Reasons for shopping:

He needs a program that will have a centralized platform for their sales leads. The systems they're using are not intuitive enough (ie: there's a lot of double-entry and too many manual processes between the two programs).

Who they've evaluated:

He has already evaluated SugarCRM and Salesforce.

Price expectations:

He is comfortable evaluating systems up to $800/employee/year or $60/user/month. They're willing to start with as many users necessary to have a solid sales automation platform in place.

Next 30 days.

column35:
7/21 - tt Bob - Delay was on deciding 3 seats vs. Enterprise.  I'll re-run agreement as 3-seat with option to upgrade to Enterprise by Sept. 15th.  That works for Bob, he'll sign that.  Created that and sent it.

7/17- lvm Bob - contract make it okay?  questions?
7/15 - good call w/ Bob, Allen, Paul - sending contract for 3 users 
7/14 - email exchange w/ Bob, Allen, and Paul Matergio - coordinating conf. call for end of this week.

7/11 - Bob emailed me back:  he's been swamped this week, we'll have to talk next week, I proposed Tuesday morning (should be able to pull that off pending travel sched.)

7/10 - lvm Bob (he was out today, proposed we connect tomorrow morning)

 

7/08 - call to Bob, no msg.  Traded emails later, from Bob:  "corporately we are planning to move ahead with Cosential.  Initally we will start off with the minimum number of licenses...".  Scheduling time to walk through next steps, this afternoon or tomorrow morning.

 

6/24 - Demo w/ Bob and Allan - they were impressed.  Had been trialing Zoho, it is not quite what they want.  They need transparency/visibility on interaction history, ease of reporting.  Have one proposal writer. Discussed possibility of adding "proposal Project Initiation Sheet" ("PPIS" - a fillable PDF) to Cosential to one degree or another... maybe set a workflow trigger that it needs to be filled out.  (Attach it to that email notification, perhaps?  If not, have it sitting in documents tab?  Maybe populate the fields to a Sammy survey that goes out automatically?).  Talked pricing a bit, they asked specifically about adding users mid-stream.  $3200-$6700 for implementation, biggest variable is $2500 FDC.  Need to discuss internally.  At least one other partner would need to be involved in discussion.  They will reach out to me next week to discuss next steps. 

6/20 - traded emails w/ Bob, confirmed Tuesday 11 am demo time.
6/18 - new demo lead from Bob Hoad.  Emailed him letting him know I talked with Allan (cc'd Allan), and proposed demo times (since I haven't heard from Allan on scheduling). Closed duplicate Robert Hoad lead.

6/13 - tt Allen.  40-person firm, 10-12 folks with biz dev responsibilities.  Using a Sage accounting platform now.  2 corporate initiatives:  1) re-branding, scheduled to be completed August 1.  2) Institute company-wide business development database, w/ sector groups, firm divisions, etc. (ideally, align this w/ re-branding launch).  Talked about implementation - what it entails, timeline.  Firm does not have CRM at moment, track most things in Excel.  Consulting firm, 3 divisions:  Engineering for buildings (comml/res/industrial/institutional); Agribusiness Group (big ag companies like Cargill, Vitera - working mostly w/ them on Canadian prairies, some work in Cargill World HQ in Minnesota); Environmental Consulting.  Those three divisions have some of their own processes/best practices, but they want better company-wide stuff.  Half of work referred, but do some proposals/RFP response.  Prime sometimes, sub-consultant other times.  Allan is one of three owners.  The Eval/Decision team:  All three owners plus the three National Leads (leadership of divisions).  Wanted a demo account to kick the tires, told him we can't do it.  Scheduling demo via email for the six of them.

column35:
7/11 - redlines in Notes on new copy of agreement, sent to Grace, spoke about it, that looks good, she is sending to Chris.  May be Monday before he tackles it.

7/10 - she sent Chris Chivetta's redlines, we're reviewing this afternoon.  Talked through them with Grace - we should be in good shape on everything, she didn't seem put out that we're unwilling to modify our limitation of liability.  On the Prof. Svcs. Exhibit, she can send me a paragraph/clause/redline that gets them comfortable with it and we'll be good (per Dan).  She said she'll send that today, she'd like me to revamp the contract to reflect redlines, she'll send to Chris to sign.  He is out of office until mid-next week, but she thinks she can talk with him this weekend and get him to execute via e-signature -  they're eager to get started, have already hired an intern or two to do some data entry.  

7/09 - Grace was out last week, lvm today.  Grace LVM for me later in the day - they are waiting for Chris Chivetta to sign the agreement; he has been in and out of the office for the last week+, working to get his attention.

6/27 - Carrie called - Michelle and Grace are both out, so she has done reference calls.  Answered questions on implementation timeline, initial Cosential commitment (it is one year - no outs).  She asked for contract for 3 full, 2 read-only, including Deltek Vision FDC.  Christopher Chivetta is authorized signer.  She will push for a signature in the next day or two, but chances are remote to pull it into June.  Likely July close.

6/19-  Sent reference intro email to Mike Conner of Bohlin Cynwinski Jackson (who reports that his firm is partnering w/ Hastings + Chivetta on a project at Wash U. in St. Louis).  Also talked to Denise Sweeden, got green light, sent reference intro email to her and Michelle/Grace as well.  Have green light from Kathy Kalt of DAG Architects - she's a HUGE fan of Cosential, but only uses for proposal automation... may intro Kathy in a few days w/ the caveat that she is just proposal person, but may give them some perspective on how to incorporate that down the road.  

6/18 - tt Michelle - Keeping Deltek is 95% off the table - they are planning to choose between AEC360 and Cosential.  AEC360 has no proposal automation, right? That is no longer the top priority for them - biz dev/lead/pipeline mgmt more important, although she thinks Cosential's proposal automation is great and they would likely use it eventually - but that's secondary concern.  Getting references over to her, the firm principal still wants recommendation before EOM.  Michelle out much of next week, Grace Nordmann may be the one making calls to references, intro both of them in emails.  

6/17 - Traded emails with Michelle - she requested pricing breakdown and references.  Wasn't able to reach her by phone, but emailed detailed pricing breakdown (implementation:  $5610, including the $2500 Deltek FDC).  

6/12- Demo w/ Michelle Gray, Tarah Smith, Grace Nordman, and Carrie (all in marketing), plus Dale Harvey (Business Development). Went well - new mobile w/ geographic search was well-received (in screenshot form).  Key things:  better tracking of opportunities/leads/clients, streamline processes.  They will discuss, we'll reconnect early next week to talk next steps.  Gave pricing overview in broad strokes.

6/11 - talked w/ Michelle, Qualfied Lead.  They use Deltek Vision for accounting, have CRM module but find it not user-friendly, and have regressed to using Excel to track leads/pursuits.  50 person firm. Use Outlook.  MOBILE is critical for them - want to hear about that.  4 people in Marekting department, one BD Director.  Those 5 will be on demo tomorrow, their boss has requested a CRM recommendation by July 1st.  3 options - stick w/ Deltek, invest in Cosential, invest in AEC 360.  Proposal automation important.  Respond to about 100 RFPs per year, which accounts for half their business, the other half from existing relationships.  The boss - ultimate DM - will not join us for demo, unable to get him involved.  No firm implementation timeline.  Budget TBD.  Scheduled 1:30 pm demo on Thursday, 6/12.

Email: mgray@hcarchitects.com
Phone: 3148635717

column35:
8/19 - got final seat count from Matthew, sent agreement (8 full, 3 r-o, plus Sage 300 FDC).  Signature/payment this week.

8/06 - line up refs and answers to questions, lvm Katie trying to confirm seats so I can complete proposal.

8/05 - good demo w/ CEO

7/23 - traded emails, sent webinar links.  Connect with Katie on 8/04 - we'll plan into to Dave Shiutler (CEO) and/or another demo if people can't attend 8/06 webinar.  Katie emailed back proposing wednesday, 7/30, but I'll be at Build Business - any dave-friendly dates the following week?

7/22 - emailed re: scheduling next steps

7/10 - lvm Katie - let's talk next steps.

7/02 - looks like we didn't have any US2 folks attend the webinar, although Katie registered.  LVM for her - if they weren't able to make it, can we schedule an alternative?

6/20- demo with Katie, Matthew, Charlie Pickett (sales), Larry Ward (sales), and Simone Sanders (proposals, database?).  Went very well - efficiency aspects appealing, integrations, minimizing typing/data entry, mobile application.  Simone had lots of technical questions - integration with a lead service that I wasn't familiar with (not FedBizOps, might have been FedBid?), we don't have an integration, but they can import via spreadsheet.  Sent Simone FDC installation guide.  Larry (or Charlie?) asked about "dragon naturally speaking" dictation-to-text software, they'd love to have some kind of integration like that someday.  Jed to connect with Katie in next couple of days for feedback and next steps.  We didn't get much past the Opportunity level in the demo (lots of focus on grid views/tasks/integrations), may want some time to show Proposal Automation, although that functionality is secondary to them.  Follow-up questions for me to track down answers:   1) can we sync from Cosential to a "group" calendar in Outlook? [also - jed to get detail on calendar sync in general... is that only for 'events'?  not sure];  2) Can tasks be created/assigned through the mobile application?;  3)  Is our iOS application "universal" (optimized for both iphone and ipad), or not (meaning it was built specifically for one or the other, and runs in some kind of "compatibility mode" in the other?).  

Talked w/ Katie after demo, answered a question from CFO (yes, he would need a Cosential login to view sales projections in Cosential... either Full license if he wants to manipulate things in Goals module, or Read-Only if he just wants a quick look at pipeline).  Katie thinks that Cosential is the ideal fit for the firm.  In order to get a signature, she is certain SOMEONE from our firm (me, maybe Reid if he is in town?) will need to meet CEO & President David Shutler (Dave) in-person in Dallas.  Talked details of implementation and timing.  Timing would be perfect for them for a July signature - Katie will be OFA, she has free time through SEptember.  Sales is super-busy through September (aligning to Federal Gov't's fiscal year end 9/30), but will have time to train after October 1.  Late July signature, maybe early August, and 12 weeks implementation will be great.  Will likely need to talk with Ops department - I think they are the folks who do a lot of entry/maintenance on business they've won.  Next step:  Dave and folks from Ops to attend July 3rd CRM webinar (Dave is OOO until June 30th, couldn't do anything until then anyway), that will prompt questions and deeper dive.  Sent registration link.  Dave was originally scheduled to be on call today but had a flight and couldn't make it.

6/10 - exploratory call with Matthew and Katie Troy.  Need their systems to talk to one another - systems w/ project info, lead info, etc.  Want to tie proposals/projects/experience together, give everyone access to things quickly.  (Go/No-Go not important).  Katie needs to do reporting, as well.  HAve homegrown filemaker system for key sales & operations contacts).  Using Sage 300 for accounting.  Do mostly work w/ VA Hospitals (regional divisions around the country), they get to know the energy managers @ those places, cultivate relationships, get more work.  Respond to some RFPs, but as few as possible.  Have a consulting firm they work with who filters through the federal gov't stuff and feeds them the things that fit... they are a Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business, so they are able to get a lot of work through that status.  Do lots of SF330s, especially for Army.  On proposals, seems like they are pulling pages from Word/PPT and putting into PDFs.  Simone, new bid writer, is handling some proposal stuff.  Sales team is on the road, need something easy to update.  23-ish people in-office, they may want 10 or so seats.  Talked pricing, implementation, qualfied on price.  Sales team has a "wish list", we'll need to get their buy-in.  Next step:  demo for firm owner,some members of sales team on Friday, 6/20.  No specific timetable (although some people want it "yesterday"), but would want something implemented in 2014.   Katie has used SFDC, they are looking into that as well, discussed differences - she understand that it would require some customization.  Emailed w/ confirmation that we have integration for Sage 300, included FDC overview and WhyCosential.

Attended CRM Live Webinar - based in Dallas

column35:
5/30 - Great demo with Celeste, Pam, and Sabrina.  Feedback tremendous - "this solves all of our problems!".  Sending pricing overview, link to recorded SF330 webinar.  Celeste will review pricing/seat options with Sabrina, please call her back on Wednesday (she'll be in staff meeting until 11-ish, try after that).  Great shot for June close, per Celeste - Sabrina will want to move ASAP once she has decided.  

5/23 - Scheduled demo for 10 am CDT on Friday, 5/30.

5/22 - long convo w/ Celeste.  Soundsl lie a great fit.  Will need to get Sandra's buy-in, she'll have to approve budget. Celeste has heard good things about Cosential for years at SMPS events. Challenges w/ current systems:  Filemaker DB is inflexible, requires duplicate entry, and they've sunk a lot of money into trying to make it work better for them, unsucessfully. Contacts in Outlook and contacts in Filemaker don't sync.  InDesign non-ideal as resume information storage place - requires extensive data entry, time. Celeste doing analytics manually in Excel.  Have no current formal Go/No-Go process, Celeste trying to implement one (5 questions) right now because they are spending too much time "chasing rainbows".  Celeste will email me about demo next week with her, Sandra, and Pamela.  Will need to satisfy Pamela on tech issues (security/backup), integrations.  Sandra: make compelling case... efficiency, information flow, transparency, and analytics/reporting/pipeline/forecasting.  Sub-contractor 98% of the time, often sub on competing bid teams going after same projects. 

5/21 - spoke briefly w/ Celeste, she was on her way out.  We're going to do an exploratory call tomorrow for 10-15 minutes, then we'll schedule a demo that will include Celeste's manager (a she).  Emailed her my contact info, please let me know a good time to chat tomorrow.

column35:
11/04 - Marisa called - approved!  Not doing Timberline integration, but would like to start with 10 full users. 

9/30 - Joe, CFO, has been out, and HE has not talked w/ our refs yet, he wants to do that before signing.   Marisa to update me tomorrow.

8/21 - called, no msg, keep trying today.  Called again and got Marisa:  Demo audience very impressed.  One person said "They've thought of everything."  Team is meeting on Tuesday w/ VP to determine # of seats, and hopefully make final decision to move forward - we should know on Tuesday.  If not, may need one more convo w/ financial DMs.  Call her Tuesday after 3:30.  Let her know I'll be traveling W-F with limited availability, would like to get any paperwork lined up on Tuesday before I leave.  Likely Sept. close, outside chance for quick turnaround on signature next week.

8/20 - demo with Marisa & Justin, Rhonda Bligh (Biz Dev), Joe Moore (CFO), Grant Hutton (Estimator), Belinda Lassiter (Exec. Asst. to President).  Went well, Marisa found proposal components helpful.  Talked pricing, implementation fee between $3100 and $6100, depending largely on Timberline integration.  Confirmed that we can run Outlook with their Exchange 365, but they have had some firewall challenges with 365 and other applications - we always have Ethnos plug-in at desktop level, too.  Jed to connect with Marisa this afternoon for group's feedback.  
Called a couple of times in the afternoon, LVM for Marisa - will try tomorrow.

8/15 - tt Marisa, scheudled demo next week.  Large group, now ready to move things forward.

5/28 - Marisa emailed me asking if she could view the webinar Justin watched (proposal? not sure), or if we're having another one soon.  I volunteered to demo for her - asked about scheduling.
 

5/22- Justin and Marisa both attended 5/21 webinar.  TT Marisa - proposal automation would be great for her role.  They've discussed internally, and they are ready to do a serious evaluation.  Marisa on board with getting ultimate DMs on board early (VP And CFO) for at least an exploratory/intro/agenda-setting call.  They need to determine who will be on evaluation team; likely won't know all personnel involved for a week or two - a couple of folks are out of office.  She and Justin will let me know.  Emailed Justin to respond to the question he asked on demo yesterday, cc'd Marisa.  

5/13 - talked with Marisa (pr: muh-REE-suh) after she requested demo thru our website. She was not aware that I'd spoken with Justin.  Apparently their VP is the one who asked the ACI team to look into Cosential.  Marisa is Marketing Coordinator, very interested in proposals piece, also CRM.  She would likely manage a large part of Cosential if they were to buy.  I suggested she check out public demo for proposals on 5/21, then we can discuss Cosential in-depth with all of the key players when the CFO is back next week.  Other people involved in eval:  VP, Assistant to VP, maybe a few other end users.  Sent webinar registration link to both Marisa and Justin, we'll talk next week.

5/09 - talked w/Justin.  Liked public demo, they will want to take a more in-depth look, but we'll probably need to wait for a week or two - CFO will be involved, he is out of office all next week.  I suggested including all DM's on intro call initially, even if they aren't oging to be participating in extensive demo & Q&A's.  Discussed Office 365 - their email server is basically on the cloud (Exchange, but cloud, if I understand correctly).  So we probably can't integrate at that level, but they all use Outlook on their desktops as email client - we can do the Ethnos integration there.  Will probably be week of 5/19, at earliest, before I hear from them on scheduling.

5/07 - lvm and sent email proposing intro call. He called back and we chatted a bit before publc demo, which he was ready to attend.  Firm is mainly construction management.  Not really bidding, just negotiating and getting work.  No CRM at the moment - spreadsheets and an admin who keeps trak of things.  Interviewing and hiring a BD Mgr, will probalby wait until that hire before buing a CRM.  Use Timberline.  MS office.  work with schools, develpers, oweners.  Likely 5 or 6 end Cosential users, mostly do-er/sellers.  There are a couple of folks who do proposals.  can we integrate with Outlook 365, the cloud-based Outlook?

Lead From Software Advice:

Company Profile

Segment:

Construction - B2B. They are a general contractor/construction management firm. They do some design/build.

Size (Annual Revenue):

$51 million to $100 million. Around $100 million.

Number of Employees:

51 to 100 employees. 100.

Number of Users:

6 to 10 users. 6. The VP, CFO, Operations Manager, Justin, office administrator, and the new Business Development Manager would need to be users on the system.

 

Project & Requirements Overview

Applications needed:

Sales Automation

Key features needed:

Contact management, note taking, transaction tracking, automated notifications, calendar integration, and email tracking. He doesn't need any sales tracking features because they use Timberline for that. They want to know what events that client attended, the discussions they have had with them, and the last time they had a conversation.

Deployment:

Web-based

Currently using:

Timberline, Excel, and Office 365.

Reasons for shopping:

They don't track communication with clients well. They need something to get them all on the same page and to interactively help them with generating more business.

Who they've evaluated:

Prophet.

Price expectations:

$25-$65/user/month.

Timeframe:

Less than 3 months. They are in the process of hiring a Business Development Manger right now, and they would get the system in place after that person was hired.

 

Next Steps

Request:

Price Quote

Product:

Cosential

Follow-up instructions:

Call anytime.

Contact notes:

He is looking to schedule demo times. He was very easy to work with.

Qualified By:

Josh

4/30 - answered email questions from Kate.  Greg called, walked through implementation fees.  He's comfortable, will sign today.  Wants his instance live by Friday so he can get into system and poke around over the weekend, Kate starts in her role on Monday, 5/05.  Uses Procore for fee proposal/schedule of values info, discussed how he could export a schedule of values generated by Procore, upload it to Cosential, and include it in a proposal.  

4/25 - demo w/ Kate went well.  Emailed Greg to recap our call, proposed convo early next week to map out next steps.

4/23 - Greg requested contract for review, sent over, may be able to accelerate timeline to next week.

4/21 - traded emails with Kate, who apparently has not left her old job to start at Sonoran Crest yet, making demo scheduling a bit tricky.  We've settled on 10 am CDT on Friday, 4/25.

3/31 - Exploratory call w/ Greg.  Small general contractor, $12M this year, targeting $50M/year within 5 years.  Bringing on a dedicated BD manager, poised for growth.  Tenant improvement work exclusively, property management firms are their clients... medical office space, retail, class A office.  Commercial RE brokerages often refer business.  REITS/property owners, some of those are clients. Biz Dev manager they're bringing on will help open doors for them where they don't already have relationships, then PM will take over.  CRM will be a biz dev platform, does not need to interact w/ project management.  Want to track inventory in the marketplace.  Track, for property manager, how many square feet do they have?  How many sq. feet available?  They can import some of that from "costar databases" on expiring leases.  Focus exlusively on Phoenix metro market, only 25-30 clients are REALLY clients.  Some are big, like CBRE or Jones Lange Lasalle.  Want to create proposal template library.  Demo on Wednesday.  Will include TJ (Greg's partner) and Jackie (project coordinator).  Also looking at BASE (?), SFDC, Zoho.

7/07 - Natalie is meeting with Jon Gilmore on Wednesday, 7/16.  Needs to get him to sign off on spend - she anticipates no problems, expects to get this done.  Challenge we've had with this over the last month or two has really been limited bandwidth - Natalie is THE marketing department, got buried under proposals.  Optimistic that we will get this done, but they haven't been good about sticking with firm dates.

6/20 - After 2-3 weeks of no responses, Natalie finalized seats and asked for contract - 3 full, 5 R-O, including Timberline integration.  Sent agreement, asked for clarification on timing.  Ready to sign now?

5/29 - lvm for natalie after several calls, no msgs- # seats?

5/22 - finally connected with Natalie - they've been incredibly busy (deadlines, a photo shoot, etc.), but everything calms down on Wednesday, 5/28.  She wants to do this, just needs to get the green light from principal.  Will be helpful to have a contract hand.  Getting final seat count via email, will send contract.  Still possible May close, but I think June is more likely.  

5/19 - continuing to lvm and email Natalie, not been able to connect  - is this still on track for May?

5/13- lvm Natalie- ready to discuss next steps?

5/06 - Natalie requested pricing proposal, sent that along with more detail on timberline sync. 

4/22 - Natalie is out of the office until April 28th.  

4/2 - demo w/ Natalie, went well.  Wants time to digest, please find (if possible) some detail on Timberline sync.  

4/1 - Exploratory call with Natalie:  using SFDC for contact database only.  Needs:  CRM, project archive, financial system integration.  Firm principals recognize need, would like to make a decision on something by end of April.  Project data currently housed piecemeal in excel spreadsheets, Timberline, and an Access database.  Natalie is only dedicated marketing person, there is one dedicated BD guy.  They have 4 SFDC licenses, Natalie and BD guy are the only ones to really use it.  Talked pricing:  minimum 3 seats, approx $5600 implementation w/ FDC.  Natalie basically the one making decision. Heard about us through peers in the industry.  Only negative she has heard is that our training is not as robust as it could be.  Uses InDesign primarily for proposals.  Demo tomorrow, 2 pm CDT.

3/27 - spoke w/ Natalie, rescheduled our exploratory call for 9 am CDT on Tuesday, April 1.

3/18- emailed re: reschedule.

3/11- Natalie no-showed for our 10 am EDT call.  Emailed that she is having computer problems, we're rescheduling
