5/14- Valerie asked for contract June 2nd, they should be able to start then, just need to wait to get other stuff tackled first.  Proposed putting anniversary date of August 1 if we can get signature in May, that should work.  Sending her contract.

5/06 - Valerie wants 4 full-access licenses, 9 read-only.  Not sure if they're ready to sign just yet... they're finishing another project (implementation of software?) and probably don't want to sign until that is finished, maybe another week or two.  I asked her to get some clarity on that before I send over agreement (since I need to include an expiration).  (NOTE:  if she comes back with a timeline that jeopardizes close this month, I'll offer adjusted anniversary date in exchange for signature in May).

 
5/02 - Demo with principals Gary Ferguson and Tom Forney, plus Valerie.  Went well - Valerie emailed immediately afterward to let me know Tom wants to move forward.  She and Gary will determine license counts within a week or so and we'll get them a contract.

4/28 - Scheduled demo for 5/02 at 9 am CDT.

4/25 - lvm Valerie, scheduling demo?

4/22 - Valerie reports that Gary is on board, other principals hesitant, want one more demo.  Working with her on scheduling.

4/18- vm for Valerie - feedback?  Moving forward?

4/15 - emailed - how did it go this morning?

4/14- traded emails w/ Valerie - she asked for screenshots for a presentation to exec team tomorrow morning at 6 am (!).  Sent screenshots, said she doesn't need anything else, will let me know how it goes tomorrow.

4/8 - Traded emails with VAlerie on pricing options, she'll discuss internally to determine seats.

3/28 - demo w/ team

3/27 - pushed demo to 3/28.  Shared Ethnos info w/ Scott.  They are targeting 3 full-access users and between 5 and 10 read-only users.  3/28 demo will include Gary (president) and Cameron (role TBD, based in Dallas).

3/25 - traded emails with Valerie Noel, tentatively scheduled demo for 3/27, 10 am CDT.

3/17 - tt Scott - likely won't be able to set up a demo until next week (week of 24th).  In the meantime, I need to check on our Outlook plugin - Scott's IT guys want to take a look at that or learn a bit more detail about it.  Sent pricing overview via email.

2/28 - Demo w/ Scott, Ruby, and Valerie.  Ruby's focus is on sending Contracts to subs. She had to leave early, but I showed ability to build lists of subcontractors by discipline/company type, export to Excel, and how that could be used for Mail Merge into Word contracts.  
Scott and Valerie really liked system, particularly proposal generation.
Up next:  demo for firm principals (Tom & Suzannne?).  Important to them: using Cosential as internal storage for resumes and projects long term; Lead Tracking; possibly mobile.  I can gloss over the Proposal stuff with the principals.  Jed and Scott to coordinate demo times via email.


2/25 - lvm Scott re: demo scheduling.

2/21 - emailed Scott re: demo times next week?

2/19- Had intro call with Scott, Ruby (handles subs/bids), and Valerie (handles proposals).  Using Act 2010 CRM, which does not work with their new Office 2010. They do extensive work through a terminal server, soliciting bids (I think) from large groups of subcontractors, many of them pre-qualified. In ACT, they have those groups sorted by trade (e.g., drywall, HVAC).  They'll attach project specs/drawings to an email and blast it out to everyone a list. They want to be able to do that in Cosential, or something similar. Valerie interested in proposal automation & estimating (she does not have an estimating platform... uses InDesign). Ruby handles "hundreds of contracts per month", normally using a standardized form, and is accustomed to mail merges in Word (I think)... if we could help with that, great.  
Also looked at SugarCRM and ACT 16 - neither appears to do what they want.  Timeframe: asap.  These three folks are evaluation team, tey will make a recommendation, then we'll get the money folks involved (Alberto & Suzanne, if I understand correctly).  
Scott emailing me a couple of options for demo times next week, I'd like to include Matt or Dan or Reid on that demo.

2/06 - good demo w/ Heather, Joh, Erin, Michelle, Iris.  Heather reviewing T&C's, should be ready to go mid-next week, barring any unforseen hiccups.  

2/04 - talked w/ Heather - Michelle was on CRM live demo, but we got cut off mid-stream.  Wants to do one demo w/ Michelle, Principal, and Office Manager (who is also Principal's exec asst and will be their 3rd Cosential user) on Friday at 11 am.  Sent meeting invite.  

2/2- tt heather, ready to get this kicked off, budget approved.  May want to do a quick demo for principal, but probably not necessary.  May get it locked up at end of this week, but definitely February deal.  Heather OFA.  Michelle (marketing, started 1 month ago) will be 2nd user.  TBD on 3rd.   Michelle has seen proposal automation webinar demo, will also attend the CRM live demo Wednesday.  Sending agreement, draft implementation timeline.

1/19 - although she has registered for a couple of webinars over the last few months, I haven't had luck reaching Heather.  keep trying w/ her this month, if I can't get engagement, nurture.

5/21 - lvm Heather - reminder of webinar, still trying to connect w/ her.

5/7 - haven't had luck connecting w/ heather, but let her know i'd like to chat after she (or she and Jon) take a look at demo today.

3/27 - chatted with Heather, we're targeting week of April 14th for demo w/ Jon.  Email her a week or so prior to try to get something on the calendar.

3/17 - Traded emails w/ Heather: Confirmed (per Dan) that we can waive data migration portion of implementation fee.  Heather reiterated that their window to purchase is still several weeks out.  Emailed quote for $4270 (3 full users + $2110 implementation).

3/04 - Heather emailed asking about flexibility on implementation, since they won't have any data to migrate.  Decision on Cosential pushed back a bit to April/May. I replied that we may have flexibility, I'll work on putting firm numbers together and get something over to her next week.

2/19 - emailed re: demo scheduling.

2/13 - Exploratory call with Heather.  Likes Cosential (evaluated it in November at Bailey Edwards, now a customer), needs systems and processes in place for newly-minted Marketing Department to function as they should. She is familiar with Deltek Vision proposal generation module, found it had significant limitations. Talked pricing detail - $5200 could be difficult, firm principal (John) would have to approve spend. They have little data, she is hoping we can be flexible on implementation cost. Sent overview info, she'll recommend Cosential to John, hopefully the three of us can get on a demo. Timeframe:  ASAP.  Hope to make decision this quarter.  MArketing department is Heather, plus some assistance from 2 support staff.  Heather does biz dev, as does firm principal (John).

column35:
Patty Weatherman will be OFA.

3/24 - tt Patty - check and hard copy of contract mailed last week, should arrive soon, Patty will be OFA.

3/17 - Patty emailed me:  they have elected Cosential:  4 full licenses, 4 read-only.  Called, we should have no problem getting signature by EOM.  Jud Dalton will sign, emailed agreement for $5230.

3/13- talked with Patty, provided clarification on user licenses (individual, can use from any computer).  Patty said they're close on decision, and it is looking good for Cosential.  Will be meeting on Monday to discuss, hopefully we can get decision shortly thereafter.  Still debating how many of which license type to go with.  She plans to call me on Monday.

3/04- Had pricing detail call w/ Patty & Harold.  Users, licenses vs. implemetation, etc.  They will have little to no data to migrate, are wondering if I can give them a break on data migration.  HArold also asked how their data works with Cloud solution (give it back to them if they don't renew), explained.  Checked w/ Dan, we discount implementation (by 5 hours, $1000).  Emailed Patty & Harold to let them know.

2/28 - Patty requested pricing for 10 full users and 10 read-only.  Sent pricing, see docs.

2/26 - Patty Called - asked about what happens to their data if they ever chose to not renew Cosential.  They're still in early evaluation, she'll keep me posted as they make progress.

2/17 - Demo with Patty, Harold Ellis (leading Biz Dev), and Contessa Wright.  Unable to determine which accounting system they use. Would like to make decision quickly, but are looking at other systems.  Discussed pricing.  Harold very interested in getting implementation going ASAP if they elect Cosential.  Jed to coordinate w/ Patty via email on next steps.

2/07 - Had exploratory call, scheduled demo for Monday, 2/17. (JH)

column35:
10/29 - tt hans, john jeffries will be OFA.  Hans would like to stay involved, as well.  He is ready to get started, will sign this week - he will be out on a hunting trip next week and wants this underway before he gets back. 

10/10 - emailed Hans.

10/07 - lvm Hans, will try again in the morning if we don't connect today

9/30 - tried hans a few times yesterday and today, no response

9/26 - good demo w/ Hans, sent contract for $7110, decision Monday (likely).

5/27 - per Lauren, decision on hold until mid-June due to heavy volume of work at Synergy

6/20 - Lauren reported in a conversation earlier this week that Hans has been swamped, this deal is highly unlikely for June.  Hans does not enjoy talking on the phone, per Lauren.  Emailed him to let him know I'm happy to answer questions or address concerns from Cosential's end if he has any.

5/12- no updates yet, per Lauren.

5/05 - Demo with John Jeffries and Hans Nelson and Laruen (Axium).  Focused just on proposal automation and SF330s.  Feedback positive.  They use a lot of templates, mostly Word but some InDesign. After demo, emailed Lauren info to share with them (answer to question on headers/footers/TOC/pagination in proposals; link to tutorial video for SF330).

column35:
7/29 - call w/ Cathy (see activity), addressed concerns on implementation and simultaneous implementation w/ Ajera.  Cathy said signature Monday, we're pushing for EOM - expiration of contract which includes concessions.

7/23- lvm - confirming docs got there okay monday, any questions?

7/21 - Cathy called back to discuss seats, Matt pushed anniversary date and got her to stick with 10 seats.  Jed re-sent agreement with new anniversary date, along with implementation overview, should have signature early next week.

7/17 - updated dollars to $10,520  - (matt ran contract for me while I was out - new quote 12-0453B)

7/14 - lvm, let me know a good time to reach you today

7/11 - called, no msg

7/10 - lvm Cathy, will try her in morning.

7/09 - great demo, they'll discuss internally (but I think we'll get the expanded group).  8 folks on demo:  Cathy (finance), Cara (CAR-uh), Mindy, and Bonnie (all three Marketing), Denny Sutherland & Bill Stinson (dedicated sales roles), Fred Green (president & Head of sales), and Dennis McGuire (some sales responsibility).   Talked to Cathy in advance of demo, reviewed the docs she sent me, contract terms (we'll be doing this on Cosential paper but honoring Axium's implementation quote), strategy.

7/08 - tt Cathy, rescheduled demo for tomorrow.  She gave me rundown on attendees - this call is basically to determine how many seats.  Let her know contract will be on Cosential paper.  She is sending me info to prep for demo.  

7/07 - Cathy Erwin, Director of Finance, has postponed meeting today - two DMs have a conflict, not worth doing if we can't have them on the call - we're seeking their approval to sign off on this ASAP.  Should have reschedule info today, per Cathy.

6/24- Scheduled demo w/ Cripe team (8 people will be on the call) for Friday, July 7th.  With Sean Gotter @ Axium.  Want to buy, planning to purchase that week (or within a few days of demo), need to have a few additional folks see system in action to sign off, also need to determine number of licenses.

column35:
A brief introduction. I am a consultant working with Rosendin Electric (www.rosendin.com) assisting them with the selection and implementation of a new CRM system. You were introduced to us by one of your customers and on the strength of their experience with Cosential we would like to consider your solution.

The project has been approved by Senior Management, budget has been allocated and it is a high priority for the company. As you will see from a review of our website, Rosendin is a large electrical contractor headquartered in San Jose, Ca with offices and projects throughout the United States. We have begun the process of establishing final business requirements and will be completing an RFP in the next two weeks that will outline these requirements along with a timeline for the process. The scope of this project will be concentrated on the process of tracking new construction projects through the entire sales life cycle followed up with closing the loop during the construction phase through job completion. This will be detailed in the RFP.

We have an aggressive but very achievable schedule. The RFP will be issued the week of Jan 2, 2012 and we would like to schedule a product demonstration with Cosential on the afternoon of 1/16, from 1:30 - 3:30 in the Rosendin offices in San Jose. We expect to narrow our search to final candidates the following week and make a final selection by Feb 1, 2012 and immediately enter into final negotiations. We are planning to be live using the new system no later than July 1, 2012.

Please let me know ASAP if you are interested in pursuing this opportunity and confirm the demonstration date. In order to minimize confusion internally please direct ALL communication related to this project to me. Sam Lamonica, Rosendin Electric CIO is copied on this email and is extremely concerned about the potential for confusion and impact on the timeline that out of channel communications can create. Rest assured that you and your team will have ample access to the key decision makers during the demonstration and negotiation cycle.

 I will be available to answer any questions and assist your team in preparing for the demonstration on Jan 16.

I look forward to hearing from you and working with you on this exciting opportunity.

Thanks
 

-- 

Tom Minick
415-504-1818
